        <div class="dua-box">
            <p><b>Iftar Dua:</b></p>
            <p class="arabic">اللَّهُمَّ إِنِّي لَكَ صُمْتُ وَبِكَ آمَنْتُ وَعَلَيْكَ تَوَكَّلْتُ وَعَلَىٰ رِزْقِكَ أَفْطَرْتُ</p>
            <p class="translation">"O Allah! I fasted for You, I believe in You, I put my trust in You, and with Your sustenance, I break my fast."</p>
        </div>

        <div class="dua-box">
            <p><b>Dua for Forgiveness:</b></p>
            <p class="arabic">اللَّهُمَّ إِنَّكَ عَفُوٌّ تُحِبُّ الْعَفْوَ فَاعْفُ عَنِّي</p>
            <p class="translation">"O Allah, You are forgiving and love forgiveness, so forgive me."</p>
        </div>

        <div class="dua-box">
            <p><b>Laylatul Qadr Dua:</b></p>
            <p class="arabic">اللَّهُمَّ إِنِّي أَسْأَلُكَ العَافِيَةَ فِي الدُّنْيَا وَالآخِرَةِ</p>
            <p class="translation">"O Allah, I ask You for well-being in this world and the Hereafter."</p>
